#### Is this a Bug or Feature request?:
Bug 

#### Steps to reproduce or link to a repro project:
This is my repo to reproduce the problem : https://github.com/yhnbgfd/aspnetcore2.1-bug-test

#### Description of the problem:
In a ```single-core single-threaded``` operating system, use HttpClient in an Action and loop multiple times to call another local Action. For example, the api/Values/TestGet interface in the sample code calls the API/Values/{id} interface. , After frequent calls to api/Values/TestGet, it will cause api/Values/TestGet interface to be blocked. At this time, you can only restart the application to recover.  
  
After testing, this problem does not occur in non-monolithic, non-single-threaded environments. The .net core 2.0 version does not exhibit this problem.  
  
More Detailed Test Cases View ValuesController.  
    
In my actual project, there is the await keyword(await httpClient.PostAsync), so I still can't find the cause of the problem. 

```
        [HttpGet("Test")]
        public IActionResult Test()
        {
            HttpClient httpClient = new HttpClient();
            for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++)
            {
                httpClient.GetStringAsync($"http://localhost:5000/api/Values/{i}");
            }
            return Content($"{DateTime.Now} Finish");
        }
```

